  <section id ="methodology">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col s12 m6">
        <div class="card hoverable">
          <div class="card-image">
            <%= image_tag("math.jpg", alt: "File Name Fancy", class: "img-responsive")%>
            <span class="card-title">Interest Rates</span>
          </div>
          <div class="card-content">
            <p>Rates for ARMs are determined using a probabilty distribution where the spectrum of possible outcomes begins at 2.5% and peaks at 15%. The most likely outcomes are between rates of 2.5% & 6%. Depending on the current rate, the area below/above that rate is determined. A 1..100 number is randomly generated and subtracted from the area below the incoming rate. This number is then assumed to be basis points adjustment for that year. The adjustments are summed if the ARM has adjustment periods of longer than one year.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-action">
            <!-- Modal Trigger -->
            <a class="waves-effect waves-light btn modal-trigger white-text" href="#modal1">View Graphic</a>
            <!-- Modal Structure -->
            <div id="modal1" class="modal">
              <div class="modal-content">
                <%= image_tag("trapezoid.png", alt: "File Name Fancy", class: "img-responsive")%>
              </div>
              <div class="modal-footer">
                <a href="#!" class=" modal-action modal-close waves-effect waves-green btn-flat">Agree</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col s12 m6">
        <div class="card hoverable">
          <div class="card-image">
            <%= image_tag("Taxes.jpg", alt: "File Name Fancy", class: "img-responsive")%>
            <span class="picture card-title">Tax Withholdings</span>
          </div>
          <div class="card-content">
            <p>Taxes are calculated based on the amount of loan you are seeking. The higher the loan, the higher your effective tax rate. As you progress throughout the life of your loan, your effective tax rate is assumed to increase since income generally increases over time. The lowest rate possible is 14% and the highest rate possible is 33%.</p>
          </div>
